Harness Tester Challenge – Bug Report
This document summarizes the critical and subtle issues identified in the provided schematic, PCB layout (top and bottom layers), and firmware (CY8C9560 and main test application). Each issue is presented in clear, understandable language with suggestions for improvement where appropriate.

1. Schematic Issues
No reverse polarity protection – The 12V input only has a TVS diode (SMAJ16A), which does not protect against reverse voltage. Suggestion: Use a P-channel MOSFET or diode with a fuse to protect against incorrect power connections.
Inefficient voltage regulator – The use of L7805 for stepping down 12V to 5V is inefficient. Suggest using a buck converter to reduce heat.
Missing decoupling capacitors – Many ICs (e.g., U4, U5, GPS) do not have nearby bypass capacitors. Suggest placing 100nF and 10uF close to power pins.
Incorrect capacitor value on LNA bias – C6 is only 1nF, which is too low for RF filtering. Use 10nF–100nF.
Floating GPS pins – ~RESET and ~SAFEBOOT are not pulled up/down. This can cause unpredictable behavior.
RGB LED has only one resistor – Each LED color channel (R, G, B) must have its own current-limiting resistor.
No debounce circuit on test button – Mechanical switch bounces are not filtered. Suggest adding an RC filter or handling in software.
Missing I2C pullups – CY_SDA and CY_SCL need 4.7kΩ pull-up resistors.
SD card and GPS I/O logic level mismatch – Signals from Teensy (3.3V) may not match expected logic levels of peripherals without level shifters.

2. PCB Layout Issues
No ground plane under GPS antenna – GNSS antenna (AE1) needs solid GND underneath for good reception.
Untuned RF trace – GPS antenna trace is not impedance-controlled. Suggest using 50Ω microstrip design.
No ESD protection on USB – Add protection diodes on USB D+/D-.
Missing components – Pads for decoupling capacitors and pullups exist but are not populated.
Unmarked pin 1 indicators – Important for assembly. Add silkscreen for orientation.
No via stitching – Add ground vias along signal/power traces for better integrity.
90° trace bends – Should be 45° or curved to avoid impedance discontinuities.

3. Firmware Issues
`cy.begin()` never called – This will cause the I/O expander to not work at all. Add `cy.begin();` in setup().
Reset logic keeps CY8C9560 in reset – `CY_RST` is set LOW but not set HIGH again.
Incorrect test pass condition – Harness is marked passed if any pin passes. Should pass only if all match.
Inverted test button logic – Runs test only when button is released. Suggest flipping condition.
NMEA buffer overflow risk – No bound check on `nmea_idx`. Add check to prevent buffer overrun.
Status LED logic is inverted – LEDs are off when status is active. Logic needs correction.
No debounce for test button – Can cause false triggers. Add software or hardware debounce.
No SD file management – Always writes to 'results.txt'. Could lead to overflow or duplication.
